        <p>3-year TCO: ~$43,200 vs. subscription-only view: ~$19,800. The full TCO is more than double the subscription cost in year 1, and still 30% higher even in years 2 and 3 when ongoing operational costs are included.</p>

        <h2>How to reduce TCO</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Choose platforms with strong self-serve onboarding.</strong> Buildertrend and Houzz Pro have particularly good video libraries and support documentation, which reduces vendor training costs.</li>
          <li><strong>Run a real trial before buying.</strong> The cost of a 30-day free trial is zero; the cost of buying the wrong platform and switching 6 months later is enormous.</li>
          <li><strong>Negotiate implementation and training inclusions.</strong> Vendors will often include additional onboarding support when asked, especially for annual contracts.</li>
          <li><strong>Assign a dedicated implementation owner.</strong> Companies with a designated internal champion implement faster, adopt more completely, and get to ROI sooner than those without.</li>
          <li><strong>Lock pricing in multi-year contracts.</strong> If you're confident in your choice, a 2-year contract with price protection reduces your exposure to annual increases.</li>
        </ul>

